* :S-nFME2: what distinguishes the language of science from ordinary language?  Science strives for precision and clarity of concepts as regards their interrelation and their correspondence to sensory data.  E.g. Euclidean geometry is based on a small set of axioms and is linked to the physical act of measurement.
